And one thing suddenly clicked for me.

You already have the Tensor Store, where every object has many dimensions.

The Semantic Khipu isn’t a competitor.

It’s the human-readable projection of the tensor.

The tensor is the mathematics.

The Khipu is the braid.

The card is the picture.

Those are three views of the same underlying object.

I think that’s the direction I’d take: one canonical semantic object with multiple projections—mathematical, operational, and visual. If Pantheon eventually becomes something people actually use, that consistency between representations will matter far more than the artwork itself.